Section 22


Node: Lets us run javascript server side


Node Console

	Run in terminal using command "node"
	Can run javascript from the command line
	NOTE: cannot run alert because it is not in the browser

	Run a file with node using the command line

		node <fileName>

	Or even with ruby

		ruby <filename>


NPM

	package manager for javascript
	similar to pip but for js

	npm install <package name>

	In .js file

		// "cat-me" is the package installed
		var something = require("cat-me")

		This looks for this package, and ensures that it is included from this package, stores in this variable

	The documents will tell you exactly how to run the package and what the commands will be

	